<main class="working-content">
  <div class="working-container">
    <a href="/" class="back-btn">&larr; Back to Home</a>
    <div class="working-header">
      <h1>How This Website Works</h1>
      <p class="working-subtitle">Understanding the Missing Person Finder System</p>
    </div>

    <section id="overview" class="working-section">
      <h2>System Overview</h2>
      <p>The Missing Person Finder is a comprehensive platform designed to help reunite missing persons with their families. Our system connects those who have lost someone with those who may have found them, creating a bridge between families and the community.</p>
      
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24">
            <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z" fill="currentColor"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="info-content">
          <h3>Our Mission</h3>
          <p>To provide a secure, efficient platform that helps reunite missing persons with their families through community collaboration and real-time information sharing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="user-roles" class="working-section">
      <h2>User Roles and Responsibilities</h2>
      <p>The system operates with three distinct user roles, each with specific capabilities and responsibilities:</p>
      
      <div class="role-cards">
        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24">
              <path d="M12 12c2.21 0 4-1.79 4-4s-1.79-4-4-4-4 1.79-4 4 1.79 4 4 4zm0 2c-2.67 0-8 1.34-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.66-5.33-4-8-4z" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Public Users</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Browse missing and found person cases</li>
            <li>Report found persons in near by station</li>
            <li>Contact case administrators</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24">
              <path d="M16 11c1.66 0 2.99-1.34 2.99-3S17.66 5 16 5C14.34 5 13 6.34 13 8s1.34 3 3 3zm-8 0c1.66 0 2.99-1.34 2.99-3S9.66 5 8 5C6.34 5 5 6.34 5 8s1.34 3 3 3zm0 2c-2.33 0-7 1.17-7 3.5V19h14v-2.5c0-2.33-4.67-3.5-7-3.5z" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Registered Users</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>All public user capabilities</li>
            <li>Report missing persons in near by station</li>
            <li>Access personal dashboard</li>
            <li>Receive case updates</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24">
              <path d="M12 1L3 5v6c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 9 12 5.16-1.26 9-6.45 9-12V5l-9-4zm0 10.99h7c-.53 4.12-3.28 7.79-7 8.94V12H5V6.3l7-3.11v8.8z" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Administrators</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>All registered user capabilities</li>
            <li>Manage all cases</li>
            <li>Update case status</li>
            <li>Verify reports</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="reporting-process" class="working-section">
      <h2>Reporting Process</h2>
      <p>The system handles two types of reports: Missing Person Reports and Found Person Reports. Each follows a specific process:</p>
      
      <div class="process-cards">
        <div class="process-card">
          <h3>Missing Person Reports</h3>
          <div class="process-steps">
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">1</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Registration</h4>
                <p>Parents or guardians must register an account to report a missing person.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">2</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Report Submission</h4>
                <p>Submit a detailed report including:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Missing person's name, age, and gender</li>
                  <li>Last seen location and date</li>
                  <li>Recent photo (if available)</li>
                  <li>Description of clothing and appearance</li>
                  <li>Contact information</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">3</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Administrator Review</h4>
                <p>Administrators review the report for completeness and accuracy.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">4</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Case Management</h4>
                <p>The case is assigned a status (Pending, In Progress, Solved, or Closed) and displayed in the Parent Report Cases section.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="process-card">
          <h3>Found Person Reports</h3>
          <div class="process-steps">
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">1</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Public Submission</h4>
                <p>Anyone can submit a found person report near by station without Registration</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">2</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Report Details</h4>
                <p>Include as much information as possible:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Approximate age and gender</li>
                  <li>Location where found</li>
                  <li>Date and time</li>
                  <li>Description of appearance</li>
                  <li>Contact information</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">3</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Administrator Review</h4>
                <p>Administrators review the report and attempt to match it with missing person cases.</p>
              </div>
            </div> -->
            
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">4</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Case Display</h4>
                <p>The report is displayed in the Public Reported Cases dashboard.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="case-management" class="working-section">
      <h2>Case Management</h2>
      <p>The system provides comprehensive case management tools for administrators and users:</p>
      
      <div class="feature-cards">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Case Status Tracking</h3>
          <p>Each case is assigned one of four statuses:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Pending:</strong> Newly submitted, awaiting review</li>
            <li><strong>In Progress:</strong> Actively being investigated</li>
            <li><strong>Solved:</strong> Successfully resolved</li>
            <li><strong>Closed:</strong> Case concluded without resolution</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Dashboard Access</h3>
          <p>Registered users and administrators have access to a dashboard where they can:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>View all parent-reported missing person cases</li>
            <li>View all publicly reported found person cases</li>
            <li>Track case status changes</li>
            <!-- <li>Receive notifications about updates</li> -->
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <!-- <div class="feature-card">
